Genetic Algorithms, Theory. 

Genetic Algorithms: The paper presents an approach to automatic discovery of functions in Genetic Programming. The approach involves analyzing the evolution trace, generalizing blocks to define new functions, and adapting the problem representation on-the-fly. These are all techniques commonly used in Genetic Algorithms.

Theory: The paper discusses the minimum description length principle and its application to justify the feasibility of approaches based on a hierarchy of discovered functions. This is a theoretical concept that is used to support the proposed approach.
